<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-09-20T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-09-20T08:00:00-05:00" n="522" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d522">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/425: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-20T21:00:00+08:00">September 20, 1930—9
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 21—12:25
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>834. Department’s 312, September 8, 6 p.m.<note n="67" xml:id="d522fn67">Not printed.</note> Legation has received final text of
                            extraterritoriality proposals as handed in by Lampson. There are certain
                            changes in the June 4th draft in the preamble and in articles 2, 9, 10
                            and 15. The protocol has been added. In case the British Embassy has not
                            supplied Department with text of these changes should they be
                            telegraphed?</p>
                        <closer>For the Minister:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>